{{infobox football biography | name = Frank Biggins | image = | fullname = Francis Joseph Biggins | birth_date = 24 June 1884<ref>''1939 England and Wales Register''</ref><ref>Francis Joseph Biggins, birth registered in [[Lichfield]], Staffordshire. ''England & Wales, Civil Registration Birth Index, 1837-1915''</ref> | birth_place = [[Brownhills]], [[Staffordshire]], England<ref name="1911census">Francis Joseph Biggins in Barnsley. Occupation: Footballer professional. ''1911 England Census''</ref> | death_date = 1962 (age 77)<ref>''England & Wales, Civil Registration Death Index, 1916-2007''</ref> | death_place = | height = | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | currentclub = | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = ?–1908 | clubs1 = [[South Kirkby Colliery F.C.|South Kirkby]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | years2 = 1908–1911 | clubs2 = [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]] | caps2 = | goals2 = | years3 = 1911–? | clubs3 = [[Castleford Town F.C.|Castleford Town]] | caps3 = | goals3 = }} '''Frank Biggins''' (24 June 1884 – 1962) was an English [[association football|footballer]] who played as an outside right for [[South Kirkby Colliery F.C.|South Kirkby]], [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]] and [[Castleford Town F.C.|Castleford Town]].
==Early life== Biggins was born and raised in [[Brownhills]], [[Staffordshire]], the eldest of nine children born to John Biggins, a coal miner, and Elizabeth Biggins (''née'' Wilton). By 1901, the teenaged Biggins was also working as a coal miner in Brownhills before moving to Yorkshire,<ref>1901 England Census</ref> where he boarded with Yorkshire footballer [[Harry Ness]].<ref name="1911census"/>
==Playing career== Biggins began his football career with South Kirkby<ref name="History">{{cite web|title=South Kirkby Colliery (Almost) Complete History|url=http://www.southkirkbycolliery.co.uk/player-a-z|publisher=Matthew Thomas|accessdate=31 March 2017}}</ref> before being signed by Barnsley in May 1908.<ref>{{cite news|title=Barnsley Football|publisher=Barnsley Chronicle|date=9 May 1908|page=8}}</ref> In August 1911, he left Oakwell for Castleford Town.<ref>{{cite news|title=Biggins For Castleford|publisher=Sheffield Daily Telegraph|date=31 August 1911|page=11}}</ref>
