{{Expand Spanish|Luis Martínez Noval|date=April 2013}}

'''Luis Martínez Noval''' (3 July 1948 &ndash; 29 March 2013) was a Spanish economist and politician who was a member of the [[Spanish Socialist Workers' Party]] and served from 1990–1993 as Spain's Minister of Labor.<ref>[http://www.congreso.es/portal/page/portal/Congreso/Congreso/Diputados/BusqForm?_piref73_1333155_73_1333154_1333154.next_page=/wc/fichaDiputado?idDiputado=225&idLegislatura=7 Luis Martínez Noval profile (in Spanish)]</ref> He died in 2013 in [[Oviedo]] following a fall, at the age of 64.

