{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}} {{Use Australian English|date=March 2015}} {{Infobox rugby league biography |name = Stan Brain |fullname = Stanley Vincent Brain |birth_date = 1903 |birth_place = [[Newcastle, New South Wales]] |death_date = 1969 |death_place = [[Hamilton, New South Wales]] |retired = yes |position = {{rlp|WG}} |club1 = [[St George Dragons]] |year1start = 1927 |year1end = 33 |appearances1 = 63 |tries1 = 15 |goals1 = 0 |fieldgoals1 = 0 |points1 = 45 |teamA = [[New South Wales rugby league team|New South Wales]] |yearAstart = 1925 |yearAend = 28 |appearancesA = 6 |triesA = 4 |goalsA = 0 |fieldgoalsA = 0 |pointsA = 12 |source = Whiticker/Hudson }}
'''Stanley Vincent 'Stan' Brain''' (1903-1969) was an Australian rugby league player from the 1920s and 1930s.
==Career==
Born at [[Newcastle, New South Wales]] in 1903, Stan Brain played with the [[St George Dragons]] during the club's foundation years. He played five season for the Saints between 1927-1933. Brain represented [[New South Wales rugby league team|New South Wales]] on six occasions in 1925, 1927 and 1928. He returned to Newcastle after 1932. <ref>Alan Whiticker/Glen Hudson: Encyclopedia of Rugby League Players. 1995 ({{ISBN|1875169571}})</ref>
Stan Brain died at [[Hamilton, New South Wales]] in 1969, aged 66. <ref>BDM N.S.W. search </ref>
